dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene st †Saha b Ashwin 118 (124b 12x4 1x6) SR: 95.16

dismissalComment.html: Ashwin's first wicket is the one India wanted the most, Mahela on the charge, Ashwin tosses it up a touch wider outside off, Mahela swings and misses, Saha does not, and Mahela has to walk back after an outstanding innings, he is disgusted with himself for missing the ball

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan c Rahane b Rayudu 53 (80b 7x4 0x6) SR: 66.25

headshotImage.longCaption: Axar Patel player page headshot cutout 2021

commentTextItems.html: Saha launches it over mid on to finally take India home after the late quiet period

commentPostTextItems.html: Have a look at Bishen Jeswant's stats piece as you go. That is all from this match. Good night.
Mahela Jayawardene is the Man of the Match.

Mahela: "I am surprised and a bit embarrassed to win the Man of the Match.We need to be consistent in our overall game. The way the Indians are playing, we need 300 to put them under pressure, and we are not there yet. They are putting us under lot of pressure, picking early wickets, putting us on the back foot straight away, and we are doing repair work after that."

Kohli: "That was a brilliant performance, especially with the ball, given we were one bowler short, had to string in six overs from part-timers, to restrict them to 242 was fantastic. I was not sure, I knew I had to get to 50 to get 6000, but I did not know how much faster I was from the great man [Viv Richards]. I am trying to do whatever I can on the field for the boys."

Mathews: "We flopped in our batting once again. You cannot keep repeating mistakes. 300 is  a must for Indian wickets. 240 is nothing for bowlers to bowl at. About three-four wickets fell in the Powerplay with minimum runs, which went against us. We are trying our combinations, we want to recognise our strengths and weaknesses going into the World Cup."

Dhawan: "Happy the way I was batting. Batting in a very controlled manner, enjoying the rhythm. Earlier I was getting 25-30s, now I am getting 80-90s. Once I get set, I will bat according to the situation. At times you can hit big shots, but you dont want to because of the situation."

Another one-sided game to seal the five-match series 3-0 for India. Six-wicket win to follow the six-wicket win in Ahmedabad. Both coming in the 45th over. Sri Lanka did well to stretch the innings from 158 for 7 but 242 was never going to be enough, and they were never able to put pressure on India, although they persisted with a short-ball ploy.
Ribhav Bansal: "So Saha carries on the tradition of the Indian keeper hitting a boundary to win the match for India."

dismissalText.commentary: Kusal Perera c †Saha b Yadav 4 (6b 1x4 0x6) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: that is a ripper, that has hit the pitch on short of a length and climbed and moved away past Perera at 139.2 kph, taking a thin edge through to Saha, he had to play at that line just outside off

dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara c Ashwin b Yadav 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: they have the big wicket first ball, Yadav is celebrating with a jump, not as tight a line as the one that claimed Kusal, but Sangakkara prods at one leaving him and bouncing sharply from short of a good length, and the edge is snapped up by Ashwin at first slip

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan c Rahane b Rayudu 53 (80b 7x4 0x6) SR: 66.25

dismissalComment.html: Hyderabad cheers as Ambati Rayudu breaks the partnership in his first over, Dilshan charges out again and looks to go over extra cover, Ajinkya Rahane jumps and comes down with the ball safely in his grasp, only the second ODI wicket for Rayudu

dismissalText.commentary: Angelo Mathews c Kohli b Patel 10 (14b 1x4 0x6) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: uh oh, Angelo's top edged a pull to mid off, short and angled in quick, Angelo went hard at the pull, only to sky it for Kohli to trot in and take a simple catch

dismissalText.commentary: Ashan Priyanjan c Yadav b Patel 2 (8b 0x4 0x6) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: Yadav has taken a sharp catch at mid on, another one goes in the Powerplay, Priyanjan wanted to clear mid on as he bent and swung hard, did not get hold of a quick and full delivery, and Yadav dived to his left to take it

dismissalText.commentary: Chaturanga de Silva c Dhawan b Patel 2 (7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 28.57

dismissalComment.html: it is coming apart for Sri Lanka, and Mahela can only watch from the other end, de Silva has made some room to one tossed up on leg to try and loft over extra cover, he's mishit it badly, and extra cover has settled under it

dismissalText.commentary: Thisara Perera c sub (STR Binny) b Yadav 1 (4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: Sri Lanka going down in a heap here, Thisara now, was trying to work this short of a length delivery off his pads, closed the face sooner than needed, and the leading edge popped up to extra cover

headshotImage.caption: Wriddhiman Saha player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Wriddhiman Saha player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene st †Saha b Ashwin 118 (124b 12x4 1x6) SR: 95.16

dismissalComment.html: Ashwin's first wicket is the one India wanted the most, Mahela on the charge, Ashwin tosses it up a touch wider outside off, Mahela swings and misses, Saha does not, and Mahela has to walk back after an outstanding innings, he is disgusted with himself for missing the ball

dismissalText.commentary: Seekkuge Prasanna b Yadav 29 (32b 2x4 1x6) SR: 90.62

dismissalComment.html: misses as he has a swipe at a low full toss, and Yadav hits the base of off stump for his first four-for in ODIs

dismissalText.commentary: Nuwan Kulasekara c Rahane b Kulkarni 7 (12b 0x4 0x6) SR: 58.33

dismissalComment.html: Kulkarni gets a wicket, his first in ODIs. Kulasekara looks to clear the wide long on boundary off this full delivery, Rahane is on the run from long on, keeps his eyes on the ball and takes it calmly

dismissalText.commentary: Ajinkya Rahane c Jayawardene b NLTC Perera 31 (47b 5x4 0x6) SR: 65.95

dismissalComment.html: Rahane has been bounced out, this was just outside off this time, and climbing quickly and steeply, Rahane tried to cut it, he was on the hop and late on the shot as it pinged the glove and popped up to slip

dismissalText.commentary: Shikhar Dhawan c †Sangakkara b Kulasekara 91 (79b 8x4 1x6) SR: 115.18

dismissalComment.html: Dhawan's been given caught behind in a late decision by umpire Kulkarni, Sangakkara went up right away as Dhawan tried to hook this bouncer and withdrew late, replays show it has brushed the helmet, and missed the bat, that was a sharp short ball from Kulasekara, to give him his first wicket in his last eight ODIs

headshotImage.caption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023
headshotImage.longCaption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023

dismissalText.commentary: Ambati Rayudu run out (Mathews/†Sangakkara) 35 (46b 3x4 0x6) SR: 76.08

dismissalComment.html: this is the easiest of run-outs, and Rayudu is the one walking back, he was done in the flight as he skipped out, but adjusted to squeeze it to mid off, called and kept running with the momentum, Dhawan had his eyes on the ball and held out a hand to Rayudu, who did not stop till he had passed the other end, the ball arrived to the keeper, while Dhawan and Rayudu were still remonstrating

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Gamage b Dilshan 53 (61b 4x4 1x6) SR: 86.88

dismissalComment.html: Kohli's holed out to long on as he looked to equal the scores with an attempted six, took a couple of steps out, made some room to a shortish ball and heaved it straight to long on

dismissalText.commentary: Suresh Raina not out 18 (23b 0x4 1x6) SR: 78.26
